            world, adding to its grandeur. The mosque is a symbol of tolerance
            and unity, welcoming people of all faiths to admire its beauty and
            learn about Emirati culture. Although we know this is not in Dubai,
            it’s close enough that we didn’t want to miss the opportunity to
            visit. A must-visit for anyone traveling in the region!
